parameters:
Psema the Fake Adventurer: Tch, your futile resistance...
I've had enough, I'll kill you before I [use] you!

Clea: Who do you think you are, trying to kill me?! I won't
die until I see the dragon die, no matter what!
Fake Adventurer Psema: Who do you think I am?
Fake Adventurer Psema: Kuuh, the Adventurer's Guild...!

Fake Adventurer Psema: Damn, this is a big loss if it
continues like this.
Fake Adventurer Psema: I won't forget your faces.
Clea: Please... \| don't leave me alone...
Adventurer Celis: Are you calm now?

Adventurer Celis: No... it's okay. I'm sorry for turning you
away even though you came to the Adventurer's Guild.

Clea: No, it's okay. Nobody in the village believes me
either.

Clea: They say I went crazy from the shock of my parents
being killed.

Adventurer Celis: ...So your goal is to defeat the dragon,
huh?
Clea: Do you believe me, Celis-san?

Adventurer Celis: If you look at the scar on my back, and
because nobody believes in my dream either.

Adventurer Celis: I might understand your feelings a little
bit.

Clea: Celis-san, don't you find it difficult to carry your
dreams alone?

Adventurer Celis: I became an adventurer so that I wouldn't
give up on myself and wouldn't lose to loneliness.
Clea: ...So that I wouldn't give up on myself.
Clea: What is your dream, Celis-san?
Adventurer Celis: It's a secret for now.

Adventurer Celis: If you were to have a dream that you
wanted to pursue with all your heart and soul.

Adventurer Celis: Someday, let's talk about our dreams
here...

Adventurer Celis: I think with this, you can take the exam
to join the Adventurer's Guild.

Adventurer Celis: If you truly wish to achieve your goals
with your own hands, then I'll be waiting for you at the
Adventurer's Guild.

Clea (I never imagined fighting with my own self, something
I had never even thought about)
Clea (But if no one believes in me and no one helps me)
Clea (I'll do it. I'll avenge my father and mother!)
Adventurer Celis: Can't you walk alone?
Clea: I'm fine, I can walk!

Clea (I'll become a strong adventurer like Celis-san and
defeat the dragon!)
Girl Mel: Is Clea's song over with this?
Bard: Hahaha, I said it was a special song, didn't I?
Girl Mel: Yeah, I'm looking forward to the continuation!
Girl Mel: By the way, what is the name of this song?

Bard: The name may change depending on the bard, but I'll
use my favorite one.

Bard: The story of the girl Clea, who was spoken of as the
hero of the empire... the name of her song is...!
Clea: Celis-san isn't here... I arrived first--

Clea: It's just like last time... Celis-san will appear from
the light and help us.
Swift Celis: We were the only ones who helped, right?

Clea: When I was about to be overwhelmed by fear during our
journey, the one I remembered was Celis-san, who appeared
from the light.

Clea: That's why I felt like Celis-san was always with me in
my heart, as if we were traveling together.

Swift Celis: After being controlled by Psema and fighting
alongside Clea, I felt the way Clea sees herself as an
adventurer.

Swift Celis: During the time of reclaiming the throne, I
also witnessed Clea's unique way of being an adventurer.

Swift Celis: Because you never abandon anyone, Clea already
knows what kind of person she is.

Clea: No, I still... don't know anything about myself or my
dreams.

Clea: That's because I don't have the strength to determine
who I am...
Swift Celis: No, it's not because I'm weak!

Swift Celis: Because she's kind, because she's too kind, she
just doesn't want to admit it.

Swift Celis: Even if you're in trouble, I can't come running
anymore.

Swift Celis: Kind Clea... Clea who possesses the power to
slay even dragons... Clea who cares for her family...

Swift Celis: ...You still haven't revealed who you truly
are.
Swift Celis: So, this is the last thing I can do for Clea.
Clea: Last... What exactly do you mean by that!?
Swift Celis: Realize your true 'strength', Clea!

Swift Celis: This is different from when I was being
controlled... I will fight for Clea with all my might.

Swift Celis: And... after this battle is over, let's talk
about our dreams.
Clea: I don't understand anything, I'm just lost.

Clea: Even so, I have cut through many things with this
great sword.
Clea: I have protected many irreplaceable things.

Clea: That's why I want to respond to Celis-san's feelings
in my own way, with all my might...!

Swift Celis: Thank you for putting up with my selfishness,
Clea.

Swift Celis: I've never felt so happy about someone's growth
before.

Swift Celis: My dream, you see, is to discover the legendary
continent of Crypt.

Swift Celis: It's a coincidence, but within Opro-san's
request, Clea has already fulfilled half of my dream.

Swift Celis: I have decided to quit the adventurer guild,
Futeira, for the sake of my dream.

Clea: I think that from now on, we can do requests and
adventures together... with Celis-san.

Swift Celis: Next is Clea's turn. I want to hear Clea's
dream.

Swift Celis: I want you to remember why you became an
adventurer, why you fought.
Swift Celis: Why do you feel that accepting is a betrayal?
Swift Celis: If you just need a little more courage...

Swift Celis: I want you to accept this, the adventurer guild
Futeira's mantle is a symbol of freedom.
Swift Celis: Clea, you can live more freely, you know?
Swift Celis: Because I believe that's what you want.

Clea: I've been avoiding it, even though I should have
known...

Clea: I thought that by becoming someone [else]... I would
cease to be my beloved parents' daughter.

Clea: When I was able to be a avenger, I always felt the
presence of my father and mother.

Clea: But after I fulfilled my revenge... it felt like the
bond with my parents was severed, like a thread being cut.

Clea: I should have fought the dragon to take a new step for
my own satisfaction.

Clea: I felt that it was a betrayal... a betrayal towards my
beloved parents who loved me!

Clea: That's why, even though I say I want to become someone
else, deep down in my heart, I feel like I shouldn't become
anyone...!

Swift Celis: It's okay, what did your parents want for you,
Clea?

Swift Celis: If that's the case, then the answer is already
clear. Clea, your parents wouldn't have wanted you to
agonize over who you are.
Swift Celis: I'll ask you the same question once again.
Swift Celis: What is Clea's dream?

Clea: To reduce the number of victims of irrational violence
like me, even by just one.

Clea: My dream is to fight for the people who believed in me
and protect those who believed in me.

Swift Celis: Clea, you should know what kind of person can
do that.

Swift Celis: I entrusted this mantle to a true adventurer.
Those who wear this mantle have the duty to protect freedom.
Swift Celis: Adventurer Clea, a true adventurer.

Swift Celis: My... beloved adventurer, thank you for meeting
me here.

Swift Celis: In order to fulfill my dream, I entrust you
with this mantle.

Clea: In order to fulfill my dream, I will inherit your
mantle.

Clea: You have always been the person I admired. Thank you
so much for meeting me.
Swift Celis: Let's talk about the dream that has come true.
Clea: Celis-san, I will return this to you.

Swift Celis: The temporary adventurer guild membership card
that I gave you when we first met...

Clea: Please accept this as a charm to accompany you when
searching for the legendary continent, as promised when I
find my dream.

Swift Celis: Hehe, I'm glad you remembered. We'll be setting
off on our journey in a few days, so until then, let's talk
a lot.

Swift Celis: I want to hear about Clea and the others'
journey.

Clea: Of course! I have a new house, so please come and stay
over.

Clea: I made a best friend during our journey. Please let me
tell Celis-san about everyone!

\CL After Swift CelisA few days after parting with Clea,
Swift Celis set off on a journey to the legendary continent
of Crypt. There are no records of Celis' whereabouts or
activities since the departure.

\CL In a distant future on a certain continent, two
beautiful swords were excavated. The excavated swords were
of ancient origin, causing great concern among
archaeologists.

\CL Both swords were engraved with wings, symbols of
freedom.
